byline.original: By PATRICK HEALY and SHERYL GAY STOLBERG
byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Jess Bidgood from Washington, Alan Blinder from Atlanta, Mitch Smith from Evanston, Ill., Ian Lovett from Los Angeles, Giovanni Russonello and Alex Vadukul from New York, and Julie Turkewitz from Denver.

lead_paragraph: For some, it was an inspiring moment. For others, there were chills and discomfort that this step forward in our national story was unfolding with this particular woman.

headline.print_headline: Historical Value of Clinton Win Is One More Source of Division
headline.main: Historic Import of Hillary Clinton’s Victory Is One More Source of Division

snippet: For some, it was an inspiring moment. For others, there were chills and discomfort that this step forward in our national story was unfolding with this particular woman.
abstract: Hillary Clinton's victory speech marking her historic accomplishment as first female presidential nominee of major American political party draws mixed reactions from voters; interviews with several dozens of people around country show Clinton's achievement has intensified conflicting views about her.
